Variable font must have a STAT table.

No check of STAT table for static fonts included, yet. Static fonts do not need to have a STAT table. It is only recommended by Microsoft, not required.
More infos here:
https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/typography/opentype/spec/stat

Noto Sans Ethiopic Cond Thin Regular (NotoSansEthiopic-CondensedThin.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

(NID 16 + 'Space' + NID 17) 'Noto Sans Ethiopic Condensed Thin' ≠ 'Noto Sans Ethiopic Cond Thin' (NID 1).

Pass

NID 6 is 'NotoSansEthiopic-CondensedLight', Everything looks good.

Noto Sans Ethiopic Cond Light Regular (NotoSansEthiopic-CondensedLight.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

(NID 16 + 'Space' + NID 17) 'Noto Sans Ethiopic Condensed Light' ≠ 'Noto Sans Ethiopic Cond Light' (NID 1).

Noto Sans Ethiopic Cond ExtBd Regular (NotoSansEthiopic-CondensedExtraBold.ttf)

name

MS NID 6

MS NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'NotoSansEthiopic-CondensedExtraBold', Everything looks good.

Pass

Noto Sans Ethiopic Cond ExtBd Regular (NotoSansEthiopic-CondensedExtraBold.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

(NID 16 + 'Space' + NID 17) 'Noto Sans Ethiopic Condensed ExtraBold' ≠ 'Noto Sans Ethiopic Cond ExtBd' (NID 1).

Pass

Noto Sans Ethiopic Cond Blk Regular (NotoSansEthiopic-CondensedBlack.ttf)

name

MS NID 6

MS NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'NotoSansEthiopic-CondensedBlack', Everything looks good.

Noto Sans Ethiopic Cond Blk Regular (NotoSansEthiopic-CondensedBlack.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

(NID 16 + 'Space' + NID 17) 'Noto Sans Ethiopic Condensed Black' ≠ 'Noto Sans Ethiopic Cond Blk' (NID 1).
